definition.value: An iminium betaine that consists of 4-{2-[7-(diethylamino)-2-oxo-2H-chromen-3-yl]ethenyl}pyridine-3-sulfonate carryiing a 5-carboxypentyl substituent on the pyridine nitrogen.
A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 7-methyl-3-oxooct-6-enoic acid.
A cyclitol ester that is 1L-myo-inositol bearing a indol-3-acetyl substituent at position 1.
A monounsaturated oxo fatty acid comprising 3-oxooct-6-enoic acid having a methyl substituent at the 7-position.
A hydroxyisoflavanone that is isoflavanone with hydroxy substituents at positions 2, 7 and 4'.
The 2,3,5,6-isomer of tetrachlorophenol
A chlorophenol that is phenol in which four of the hydrogens attached to the benzene ring are replaced by chlorines.
An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (24R,25R)-3alpha,7alpha,12alpha,24-tetrahydroxy-5beta-cholestan-26-oic acid.
The acetate ester of benzyl alcohol.
A propanone that is propan-2-one substituted by a phenyl group at position 1.
A germacrane sesquiterpenoid tumour inhibitor isolated from Elephantopus elatus.

An organic sodium salt that is 2',4',5',7'-tetrabromofluorescein in which the carboxy group and the phenolic hydroxy group have been deprotonated and the resulting charge is neutralised by two sodium ions.
A furanocoumarin which bears a hydroxy group at position 5.
A penicillin compound having a 6beta-(2R)-2-(methylideneamino)-2-phenylacetamido side-group.
A furanocoumarin which bears a methoxy group at position 5.
A (1->6)-alpha-D-glucan which has extra branching consisting of (1->2), (1->3) or (1->4) linkages.
An organic potassium salt having 2,4,5,7-tetrabromo-9-{2-[(ethyloxy)carbonyl]phenyl}-3-oxo-3H-xanthen-6-olate as the counterion.
A benzoate ester that is ethyl benzoate substituted by a dimethylamino group at position 4.

A quaternary ammonium salt A liphophilic dye consisting of a dication that is N,N-dibutyl-4-[6-(pyridin-4-yl)hexa-1,3,5-trien-1-yl]aniline in which the nitrogen of the pyridine moiety is substituted by a 3-(triethylammonio)propyl group and two bromide ions. It is used to selectively stain yeast vacuolar membranes with red fluorescence.
A hexosamine phosphate having the phospho group at the 1-position.
A 1-benzofuran substituted at position 2 by a (5-oxo-2-thioxoimidazolidin-4-ylidene)methyl group, and at C-5 and C-6 by heavily substituted oxygen and nitrogen functionalities respectively.
A monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from the removal of a proton from the carboxy group of flufenamic acid.
A benzofuropyranochromene that is 1,2-dihydro-6H-[1]benzofuro[3,2-c]furo[3,2-g]chromene substituted at positions 6a and 9 by hydroxy groups and at position 2 by a prop-1-en-2-yl group.
A group derived from difluoromethane by removal of a hydrogen atom.
